</taxonomicName>
was described (
<figureCitation box="[272,434,914,937]" captionStart="FIGURES 6 − 14" captionStartId="2.[151,258,1790,1812]" captionTargetBox="[267,1309,206,1740]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[255,1324,191,1744]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 6 − 14. Dervishiya, adults and male genitalia: 6. D. sindhi Yakovlev &amp; Saldaitis sp. nov. holotype, male; 7. D. sindhi Yakovlev &amp; Saldaitis sp. nov., paratype, male, Pakistan, Sindh prov., near Sanghar, Shahdadpur, 28. 0 3. 2009, leg. Azeemi (Museum Witt, München); 8. D. sindhi Yakovlev &amp; Saldaitis sp. nov., paratype, female, Pakistan, Sindh prov., Mirpurkhas, 20. 0 3. 2009, leg. Azeemi (Museum Witt, München); 9. Male genitalia of D. sindhi Yakovlev &amp; Saldaitis sp. nov. (paratype, GenPR MWM: 25303); 10. D. cadambae Moore, 1865, male, syntype (Museum für Naturkunde, Leibniz Institut für Evolution und Biodiversitätsforschung, Berlin); 11. D. cadambae Moore, 1865, female, syntype (Natural History Museum, London); 12. Male genitalia of D. cadambae Moore, 1865 (Pakistan, Indus Kohistan, GenPR MWM: 25302); 13. D. vartianae Yakovlev, 2011, male, paratype (Naturhistorisches Museum, Wien); 14. D. vartianae Yakovlev, 2011, female, paratype (Naturhistorisches Museum, Wien)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1050839/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="396">Figures 13−14</figureCitation>
) (
<typeStatus box="[461,516,914,937]" pageId="3" pageNumber="396">Type</typeStatus>
locality: Afgh[anistan]., Nimla, 
<quantity box="[885,957,914,937]" metricMagnitude="4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.0" pageId="3" pageNumber="396" unit="km" value="40.0">40 km</quantity>
SW v. Dschelalabad; distribution: Eastern 
<collectingCountry box="[151,283,949,972]" name="Afghanistan" pageId="3" pageNumber="396">Afghanistan</collectingCountry>
) (
<bibRefCitation author="Yakovlev" box="[303,469,949,972]" pageId="3" pageNumber="396" refString="Yakovlev, R. V. (2011) Catalogue of the Family Cossidae of the Old World. Neue Entomologische Nachrichten, 66, 1 - 129." type="journal article" year="2011">Yakovlev 2011</bibRefCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Yakovlev &amp; Saldaitis" authorityYear="2016" box="[486,583,948,972]" class="Insecta" family="Cossidae" genus="Dervishiya" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="396" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sindhi">
<emphasis box="[486,583,948,972]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="396">D. sindhi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from other species by the features of wings pattern and male genitalia structure: the pale grey forewings of males, thin undulated pattern on the forewing of males, the strong costal ridge with caudally directed process, and the two pairs of tapered cornuti in vesica.
</paragraph>
